inference:
$121_5 \times 11_5$

$121_5 = 1 \times 5^2 + 2 \times 5^1 + 1 \times 5^0 = 1 \times 25 + 2 \times 5 + 1 \times 1 = 25 + 10 + 1 = 36$
$11_5 = 1 \times 5^1 + 1 \times 5^0 = 1 \times 5 + 1 \times 1 = 5 + 1 = 6$
$36 \times 6 = 216$
Convert 216 to base 5:
$216 \div 5 = 43$ remainder 1
$43 \div 5 = 8$ remainder 3
$8 \div 5 = 1$ remainder 3
$1 \div 5 = 0$ remainder 1
